<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="235" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,690,2011]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1950,1975]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[343,458,1950,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucernula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[343,458,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Lucernula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the diminutive form of 
<emphasis box="[772,857,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">lucerna</emphasis>
, which means lantern in latin. 
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1363,1950,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucernula">
<emphasis box="[1221,1363,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">A. lucernula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the species with the smallest lanterns in 
<taxonomicName box="[560,667,1987,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[560,667,1987,2011]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Amydetes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
